cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the recognition of facial expressions using deep learning techniques and visual saliency maps. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves fine-tuning of a pre-trained model, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves human-computer interaction, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of visual saliency maps suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
